= The Relationship Between Al-Islām , Al-ʾĪmān (Faith), and Al-Iḥsān (Excellence) 





== When mentioned together:

When all three terms are mentioned together, each has its specific meaning:

- *Islām  refers to:* Outward actions (such as prayer, fasting, etc.)

- *ʾĪmān (Faith) refers to:* Matters of belief in the unseen (such as belief in Allāh, angels, and divine decree)

- *Iḥsān (Excellence) refers to:* The highest level of the religion.




== When mentioned separately:

When each of these terms is mentioned individually:

If Islām  is mentioned alone > ʾĪmān is included within it.

If ʾĪmān is mentioned alone > Islām  is included within it.

If Iḥsān is mentioned alone > Both Islām  and Imān are included within it.